body:
Hello :) 

In almost all my projects, being php, js, ts... I'm using `dotenv` to store some constants that may differ depending on the environment. 

But because having to prefix or suffix the env key is not ideal and doesn't really goes well with the idea of CI etc... I usually create an .env file for each environment (e.g: `.env`, `.env.prod`, `.env.staging`, `.env.development`) to override the default ones and create something specific by environment.

In hardhat, I would love to be able to do the same thing using a .env by network, and, in hardhat.config.js be able to do something like:

```js
// get the current network 
const network = arguments.network;

// load the .env file associated to this network
let path = '.env';
if (['rinkeby', 'polygon', 'mainnet'].indexOf(network) !== -1) {
  path += `.${network}`;
}

require('dotenv').config({
  path
});

/**
 * @type import('hardhat/config').HardhatUserConfig
 */
module.exports = {
    solidity: '0.7.6',
    networks: {
        rinkeby: {
            url: process.env.RPC,
            accounts: [process.env.DEPLOYER_KEY, process.env.MINTER_KEY],
        },
        mainnet: {
            url: process.env.RPC,
            accounts: [process.env.DEPLOYER_KEY, process.env.MINTER_KEY],
        },
        polygon: {
            url: process.env.RPC,
            accounts: [process.env.DEPLOYER_KEY, process.env.MINTER_KEY],
        },
    }
}

/* or even much smaller
module.exports = {
    solidity: '0.7.6',
    networks: {
        [network]: {
            url: process.env.RPC,
            accounts: [process.env.DEPLOYER_KEY, process.env.MINTER_KEY],
        },
    }
}
*/
```

Would it be possible for hardhat to make the arguments available in the `hardhat.config.js` in order to achieve something like this?

This also helps to save A LOT of if/else conditions in all the different scripts, and in CI environments, to not have a bunch of KEYS_{environment} defined.
